Context("Numeric");

#given
$F = random(4000,10000,100);
$l0 = random(2,4,.1);
$dl = random(.0001,.001,.0001);

#computation 
$eps = $dl/$l0*100;

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.01);

##############################################################
#
#  Text 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

A sample of biological material is loaded into a material-testing machine. The material is [`[$l0]`] [`cm`] long in its unloaded state. A [`[$F]`] [`N`] tensile force is applied to the material and it stretches to a length of [`[$l0+$dl]`] as a result of this force. What is the strain in the specimen when it is stretched this much?

[`\epsilon=`] [_____]{"$eps"} [`%`]  

END_PGML

